Description: Fragment of flattened handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine orange-buff; cream slip. Rectangular stamp with kantharos (or skyphos) symbol.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 181, 10. Name Diskos.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0756)
